  <h1>Impulse Control</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>Ask for “Sit” or “Place” before meals, walks, or play.</li>
    <li>Wait at doors, stairs, or thresholds until released.</li>
    <li>Pause before throwing toys or starting play—wait for calm.</li>
    <li>Always use a release word like “OK” or “Free.”</li>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    <li>✅ Reward calm decisions like looking away or waiting</li>
    <li>✅ Practice these habits daily—not just during training</li>
    <li>✅ Use delay, slow-motion games, or “zen tug” to build control</li>
  </ul>
